<!-- §0 STATE OF THE DESK -->
<section class="hero" id="state"><div class="wrap">
  <div>
    <div class="eyebrow">Markets · Credit & Funding · State of the desk</div>
    <h1>Calm spreads.<br/><em>A funding fault line.</em></h1>
    <p class="sub"><b>The call:</b> mid-cycle, corporate spreads rich-vs-history and contained, while the Iran–Gulf shock reprices the sovereign/funding edge — EM and dollar-liquidity, not yet IG/HY. <span class="dconf medium" style="vertical-align:middle">Medium confidence</span></p>
    <span class="cta-frame cta-h"><a href="/structural/watch">Open the signal board →</a></span>
  </div>
  <div class="deskpanel">
    <div class="ph"><b>Credit regime · live</b><span>— from the registry</span></div>
    <div class="metric-row">{eq.map((s) => (<div class="mcell"><div class="ml">{s.k}</div><span class={`mv num ${wvc(s.m)}`}>{fmt(s.m)}</span></div>))}</div>
    <p style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:13px;line-height:1.6">Sovereign and funding channels are repricing first; US corporate spreads stay contained — for now.</p>
  </div>
</div></section>

<div class="wrap"><div class="orient">
  <div class="read30"><div class="r30-h">The 30-second read</div><ul>{read30.map((x) => (<li set:html={x} />))}</ul></div>
