  </div></section>
); })}

<!-- §5 COHORTS -->
<section class="dsec" id="cohorts"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="sec-head"><div><div class="eyebrow">§5 · Who’s leading, who’s lagging?</div><h2>Cohort rotation — ratings &amp; sectors.</h2></div><span class="fresh-tag">structural + daily OAS</span></div>
  <p class="lead">The durable sensitivity map by <b>ratings bucket</b> and <b>sector</b>. Click a column to sort. Compression (junk outperforming) vs decompression (quality outperforming) is the regime tell; live relative-strength is feed-pending. Lead/lag tags are <i>regime-conditional, not laws</i>.</p>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto"><table class="dtbl" id="cohtbl">
    <thead><tr><th>Cohort</th><th class="sort" data-col="rate">Rates</th><th class="sort" data-col="cyc">Cycle</th><th class="sort" data-col="usd">USD</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>{cohortMatrix.map((r) => (<tr data-rate={r.rate[1]} data-cyc={r.cyc[1]} data-usd={r.usd[1]}><td class="nm">{r.s}</td><td class={`sens ${r.rate[2]}`}>{r.rate[0]}</td><td class={`sens ${r.cyc[2]}`}>{r.cyc[0]}</td><td class={`sens ${r.usd[2]}`}>{r.usd[0]}</td></tr>))}</tbody>
  </table></div>
  <div class="deep">
    <div class="tk-h" style="margin:20px 0 8px">Ratings buckets — IG → CCC</div>
    {ratingsBuckets.map((p) => (
      <details class="dcard"><summary><div><div class="dc-t">{p.s}<span class="dc-cat">{p.p}</span></div><div class="dc-s">{p.dr}</div></div></summary>
        <div class="dc-body"><div class="prof-sens">{p.sens}</div><div class="prof-rows">
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">KPIs</span><span set:html={p.kpis}></span></div>
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">Leading indicators</span>{p.leads}</div>
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">Classic risks</span>{p.risks}</div>
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">Lead / lag</span>{p.ll}</div>
        </div></div></details>
    ))}
    <div class="tk-h" style="margin:22px 0 8px">Sectors — the credit-sensitive set</div>
    {sectors.map((p) => (
      <details class="dcard"><summary><div><div class="dc-t">{p.s}<span class="dc-cat">{p.p}</span></div><div class="dc-s">{p.dr}</div></div></summary>
        <div class="dc-body"><div class="prof-sens">{p.sens}</div><div class="prof-rows">
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">KPIs</span><span set:html={p.kpis}></span></div>
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">Leading indicators</span>{p.leads}</div>
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">Classic risks</span>{p.risks}</div>
          <div class="prof-r"><span class="prof-k">Lead / lag</span>{p.ll}</div>
        </div></div></details>
    ))}
    <p class="tnote">Sensitivities are <b>framework priors for IA defaults, not forecasts</b>. OAS proxies reference the FRED ICE BofA series family; ETF proxies are for orientation, not recommendations.</p>
  </div>
</div></section>

<!-- §6 FACTORS + §7 POSITIONING + §8 CROSS-ASSET -->
{['factors', 'positioning', 'crossasset'].map((id) => { const t = T[id]; return (
